text: Hey ya'll reminder to come in at 12. Destin will join us right away so we can get moving on data viz. I figure we will order food later on afternoon or dinner time. See ya soon.

<!here|@here>: reminder of today’s goals:

Sunday goals: 
Peter, Bryan working through ALL transitions.  By end of Sunday all cubby screens should be ready for final creative critique specifc to layout, timing and transitions 
Peter, Destin to connect and refine Data Viz.  By end of Sunday all cubby screens should be ready for final creative critique specifc to layout, timing and transitions

Bryan and I are combing Jira looking for other candidates to close, pick up.
if ya’ll need a moment of zen at any point today, i’m keeping tabs on this live stream of a family of ospreys: <http://explore.org/live-cams/player/osprey-nest>

Sunday: made great headway on Data Viz and transitions.  Tomorrow when we come in review the following on the wall for Acceptance testing (9:15 de only meeting)

	.	BWB-191 Data Viz - Animate the shapes on sides of creative to help to bring this to life
	.	BWB-265 ALL TOP SWEEPS - Remove Mixed Blend mode from all of top sweep
	.	BWB-244     Data Viz - Integrate Destin's Work
	.	BWB-268 Intermittent Communication Issue 

We then spend Monday working through rest of visual stuff to give creative team ‘last looks’ on Tuesday.  Placement, timing transitions are all fair game in the creative review.  

Monday: All visual; emphasis on Transitions, lighting, Goodbye and Data Viz
Bryan has an autonomous list.  Let’s have Peter start on following blockers:
	•	BLOCKER (Peter) <https://uncorkedstudios.atlassian.net/browse/BWB-226> 
	•	BLOCKED: <https://uncorkedstudios.atlassian.net/browse/BWB-272>
	•	Then move on to Goodbye and Data Viz clean up 

Tuesday: focus on colors, dynamic content, lighting and creative review - for final comments 

Wednesday: Set plans for July 5, QA and focus on Admin 
Thursday: Feedback and QA results
